Going further in debt to pay off debt is a bad idea. Use the snowball method. Take your smallest debt and pay it off first. That will give you a boost of confidence while you chip away at your next smallest debt. Pay it off slow from smallest to largest. I had 20k in credit card debt but paid it off in 4 months with that method. I started with my smallest balance card and paid all I could on it while making the minimum payment on all other cards then each time I paid off a card, I would lock it away in my husband‚Äôs safe, lol. Idk how it works in UK but it North America, credit cards are mostly a trap if not treated like a debit card. Never spend what you don‚Äôt have in the bank to cover
